%% Diagram: WebAuthn / passkey registration ceremony
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant B as Browser
    participant A as Authenticator
    participant RP as Relying Party

    U->>RP: start registration
    RP->>RP: generate challenge, rpId, user.id
    RP-->>B: PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions
    B->>A: navigator.credentials.create()
    A->>U: verify user (biometric / PIN)
    U-->>A: gesture
    A->>A: generate keypair bound to rpId
    A-->>B: credentialId, attestationObject, clientDataJSON
    B-->>RP: POST /webauthn/register
    RP->>RP: verify origin, challenge, attestation
    RP->>RP: store credentialId + public key
    RP-->>U: registration complete

    Note over A,RP: Private key never leaves the authenticator.\nOrigin-bound credential is phishing-resistant.
